claim.claim-text:
1. A fixing member used to fix toner images, having the form of a film or belt which is multi-layer constructed to have at least a base layer, an intermediate layer and a surface layer, wherein; 
said base layer is formed of a material having radiation-transmitting properties, capable of transmitting radiation coming from a radiation source disposed on the back side of said base layer in non-contact with the fixing member; and 
said surface layer or intermediate layer is formed of a material having radiation-absorbing properties.

22. A fixing assembly for fixing toner images to an image-fixing medium, which assembly comprises: 
a fixing member used to fix toner images, having the form of a film or belt which is multi-layer constructed to have at least a base layer, an intermediate layer and a surface layer; and 
a press member disposed opposingly to the fixing member; 
a radiation source being disposed on the back side of the base layer of said fixing member; and the surface layer or its vicinity of said fixing member being heated by radiation coming from a radiation source, and pressed, at the time the image-fixing medium passes through a fixing nip formed between said fixing member and said press member; 
said base layer being formed of a material having radiation-transmitting properties, capable of transmitting radiation coming from a radiation source disposed on the back side of said base layer in non-contact with the fixing member; and 
said surface layer or intermediate layer being formed of a material having radiation-absorbing properties.
